  <description><![CDATA[<p>We think Hotel Capri is one of the best places to watch the sunset on <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a>. It’s on the edge of the rocks so you get uninterrupted views of the lake – especially from the restaurant’s terrace.</p>
<h2>A warm welcome by the lakefront</h2>
<p>The hotel’s been managed by the Bergonzini family for three generations. They're very welcoming and go out of their way to make sure you have a good time. We always stop here for an aperitivo and some delicious pasta when we’re in town. The hotel's in a great position just 100 metres from the lakefront and a five-minute walk from the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce" href="/{localLink:umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce}" title="Malcesine">Malcesine.</a></p>
<h2>Sit back &amp; relax by Lake Garda</h2>
<p>You’ll notice the gardens as soon as you arrive – grab a lounger on the grass and enjoy some peace and quiet. The pool is close by when you need to cool off. Or, head to the spa and take a dip in the whirlpool.</p>]]></description>
